  "summary": "Malicious code in ppt-creator (npm)",
  "details": "Ppt-creator@1.0.0 is a malicious package that exfiltrates system data at install time. The preinstall hook (node index.js) runs during npm install, collecting the victim's hostname, username, home directory path, DNS server list, and the contents of /etc/passwd and /etc/hosts. This data is sent via HTTPS POST to 3z3l99x7vp8us6lzqm575hfh58bzzqnf[.]oastify[.]com (a Burp Collaborator endpoint). The package contains no legitimate functionality.",
